      "writtenOn": "2020-10-21T00:08:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Btw these descriptors we generate are awfully inefficient. They contain not only protos of e.g. buildbucket.v2.Builders, but also all transitive dependencies. As a result, we have a ton of copies of e.g. proto.Empty descriptors scattered through out pb.descriptor.go files.\n\n(It is also the reason why the actual byte blob hasn\u0027t changed in this CL: the full descriptor set with all dependencies is unchanged, it still has all the crap).\n\nI investigated deleting them. Their only real purpose right now is to preserve comments of proto messages and methods that we can see in RPC Explorer. Descriptors generated by protoc natively have them stripped :(",
